Package Notes

Class ChecklistNote

java.lang.Object
Notes.ChecklistNote
All Implemented Interfaces:
NoteInterface
public class ChecklistNote extends Object implements NoteInterface
Holds data for a checklist note(content and type). It also provides ways to manipulate that data in various ways. Note the array is a TextItem Array, so each item can hold data about if the item is and if it is checked or not.
Author:
Nick Pehl, Cam Lettieri

    • ChecklistNote

      public ChecklistNote()
      This is a constructor for a Checklist Note object. It takes no parameters. It sets the type to NoteType.CHECK, and it makes the contentArr[][] a 1X1 array.

      Description copied from interface: NoteInterface
      This method gets the full content[][] Note that the size of the Array is going to be different depending on the class you are using. Default it will be a [1][1] Array no matter what.     • editContentSize

      public void editContentSize​(int rows, int cols)
      Description copied from interface: NoteInterface
      Changes size of the 2D array. This keeps data the same in existing locations. For example, if you had data in [2][3] and in [4][3] and you called editContentSize(3,3). The data in [2][3] would stay the same, but data in [4][3] would be deleted. This method does different things depending on the class you are using. Default: method does nothing because there is only one valid location [0][0], and you can't change that. Checklist: edits size to [rows][1] (i.e. col param does nothing) Table: edits size to [row][col]
      Specified by:
      editContentSize in interface NoteInterface
      Parameters:
      rows - new number of Rows
      cols - new number of Columns
